      "role": "user",
      "content": "i dont want magic or a different version of the story. i'm just tired of the walking. i keep looking at the edge of these cliffs or the deep water in the harbors and thinking how easy it would be to just step off the path and stop being a traveler. like, instead of continuing to wander around looking for something that isn't there, why not just complete the journey? why is staying on the path the only \"right\" way to do it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
